## Key Findings & Clinical Reality

### 1. The Ceiling of Behavioral Data
When restricted strictly to historical and behavioral data (Age, Smoking, STDs), all models struggled to separate the positive cases from the negative cases. The distributions overlap too heavily; a high-risk lifestyle does not mathematically guarantee a positive biopsy, and a low-risk lifestyle does not guarantee a negative one.

